to the editor president clinton deserves credit for using his executive authority to help protect our precious coastlines news article may 27 on a deeper level the united states can show significant leadership by finally ratifying the 1982 united nations convention on the law of the sea the law of the sea treaty already in effect with 133 members includes many provisions relating to a variety of maritime interests including shipping defense and maritime safety and marine environmental protection in 1994 a separate agreement addressing the united states concerns over the deep sea bed provisions failed to produce our ratification presently only partisan politics in the senate impedes membership howard s schiffman brooklyn may 27 2000 the writer is an international lawyer

